          <source>Security is top-of-mind for most people working in technology, and this is especially true when it comes to software.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="102" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>It seems we are constantly hearing about companies and governments that we entrusted our private data to, being compromised.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>When this happens - either maliciously or accidentally, it costs them customers and, ultimately money.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Did you know that the most common cause of data breaches is poor security in software?</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>It's true.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>This means that the pressure is on for software developers to be more diligent than ever.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>But where do they begin?</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>This module is the start of your journey into the world of application security, with the top five defenses for web applications.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Learn how to secure your web applications on Azure and protect your apps against the most common and dangerous web application attacks.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="110" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Learning objectives</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="111" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In this module, you will:</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="112" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Use Azure Security Center</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="113" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Verify your application's inputs and outputs</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="114" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
